From 0f6408cc0aeb5a4d70f5ec5875ad6792baa154af Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Brandon Day <brandon@daysllc.com>
Date: Tue, 17 Mar 2026 06:14:27 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] fix: address all critical + high audit findings from forensic
 audit

Round 1 (Critical data integrity):
- Fix document filename IV not stored (file_name_iv column + save/read)
- Rebuild password rotation as full rekey (re-encrypts items, docs,
  search indexes; generates fresh KDF salt; clears biometric data)
- Implement real account deletion via server-side API route

Round 2 (Security & trust):
- Remove broken biometric unlock from UI until server-side WebAuthn
- Fix PWA assets blocked by auth middleware (manifest + sw.js)
- Fix password shown as plaintext in AddItemModal (type=password + toggle)
- Normalize auth errors to prevent user enumeration
- Add security headers (CSP, X-Frame-Options, Referrer-Policy, etc.)

Round 3 (Build health):
- Fix build-time env var crash (defer throw to runtime)

Round 4 (Extension):
- Add SAVE_OFFER handler with duplicate detection and pending save flow
- Add GET_PENDING_SAVE, CONFIRM_SAVE, DISMISS_SAVE message types

Also includes:
- Supabase migration for file_name_iv column
- New lib/auth-errors.ts for error normalization
- New app/api/account/delete/route.ts for real deletion

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
